                            <comment id="13620899" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Wed, 3 Apr 2013 13:12:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please find attached file &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-195&quot; title=&quot;log files in async module&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-195&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-195&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It contains fixed JUnit test and config xml resource files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that one of these tests, FastRollingFileAppenderRolloverTest, depends on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-193&quot; title=&quot;RollingFastFileAppender (in log4j-async) does not roll over&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-193&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-193&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625033" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Sun, 7 Apr 2013 22:19:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I applied the patch in revision 1465483. However, I had to comment out 1 line in FastRollingFileAppenderRolloverTest as it is failing with the stack trace below.  In addition all of the test classes and ClockFactory were missing Apache License headers so I added them. Finally, I noticed that when I generated the web site the async project has over 70 checkstyle errors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running org.apache.logging.log4j.async.appender.FastRollingFileAppenderRolloverTest&lt;br/&gt;
Tests run: 1, Failures: 1, Errors: 0, Skipped: 0, Time elapsed: 0.453 sec &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt; FAILURE!&lt;br/&gt;
testRollover(org.apache.logging.log4j.async.appender.FastRollingFileAppenderRolloverTest)  Time elapsed: 0.397 sec  &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt; FAILURE!&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.AssertionError: No more lines&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.junit.Assert.fail(Assert.java:91)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.junit.Assert.assertTrue(Assert.java:43)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.junit.Assert.assertNull(Assert.java:549)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.logging.log4j.async.appender.FastRollingFileAppenderRolloverTest.testRollover(FastRollingFileAppenderRolloverTest.java:72)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625034" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Sun, 7 Apr 2013 22:29:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rats. I didn&apos;t see the note on the dependency on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-193&quot; title=&quot;RollingFastFileAppender (in log4j-async) does not roll over&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-193&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-193&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625035" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Sun, 7 Apr 2013 22:34:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be great if you could look at that one too... &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Apologies for the missing headers and I&apos;ll look at the checksite output. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625041" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Sun, 7 Apr 2013 23:00:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After applying the patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-193&quot; title=&quot;RollingFastFileAppender (in log4j-async) does not roll over&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-193&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-193&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the unit test no longer fails.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625190" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 8 Apr 2013 06:32:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Confirmed. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
